excerpt: Indoor market established in the 1960s with stalls selling produce, seafood & household goods.
detail_description: Seogwipo Olle Market is an indoor market that has been around since the 1960s, offering a variety of stalls selling fresh produce, seafood, and household goods. Located in Seogwipo, the second-largest city on Jeju Island in South Korea, this market is part of a region known for its rocky volcanic coastline and stunning natural landscapes.
name: Seogwipo Maeil Olle Market
address: 18 Jungang-ro 62beon-gil, 특별자치도 Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: A walk in lush natural surrounds with shops & food stands leads to this scenic waterfall & park.
detail_description: Cheonjiyeon Waterfall is a picturesque natural attraction located in a lush park area with shops and food stands. The name "Cheonjiyeonpokpo" means "sky connected with land," reflecting the heavenly appearance of the waterfall as it cascades down. The surrounding wooded area is home to diverse flora, including rare plants like brambles, songyeopnan, gusiljappam trees, sanyuja trees, and camellias.
name: Cheonjiyeon Waterfall

excerpt: Oceanside 75-ft. waterfall cascading from a cliff, with its waters flowing into the sea.
detail_description: Seogwipo Jeongbang Waterfall is a stunning 75-ft. cascade that plunges directly into the ocean, making it the only waterfall in Korea to do so. While swimming isn't recommended, visitors can wade into the water and get close to the waterfall during low tide. The surrounding area offers picturesque views of Sojeongbang waterfall from an observatory and provides a perfect spot for a picnic lunch on the rocks near the water.
name: Seogwipo Jeongbang Waterfall

excerpt: Casual dorms & private rooms in a cool hostel featuring a cafe, a courtyard & complimentary Wi-Fi.
detail_description: Mido Hostel is a trendy accommodation located in the vibrant city of Seogwipo, just a short walk from Olle Traditional Market and Lee Jung Seop Art Street. The hostel offers both single-sex dorms and private rooms, all featuring bunk beds with amenities such as private curtains, reading lights, and sockets. Renovated in 2015, the hostel boasts a peaceful atmosphere popular among Koreans.
name: Mido Hostel

excerpt: Modern, cable-stayed pedestrian overpass with a sail-shaped tower, illuminated at night.
detail_description: Saeseom Island Saeyeongyo Bridge is a modern, cable-stayed pedestrian overpass with a sail-shaped tower that lights up beautifully at night. It connects to Saeseom Island and offers stunning views of Seogwipo port area. The island itself is known for its natural beauty and is a great spot for birdwatching.
name: Saeseom Island Saeyeongyo Bridge
address: 40 Namseongjung-ro, Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Dramatic cliffside views are the highlight of this scenic lookout point with trails & swimming.
detail_description: Oedolgae, also known as Independence Rock, is a striking sea stack located off the coast of Jeju. Rising 20 meters above the sea, this freestanding rock formation offers dramatic cliffside views and can be easily accessed via a short walking track. Situated in the southern part of the island, it is a popular spot for visitors to enjoy its photogenic beauty throughout the day. To avoid crowds and capture the best light, early morning or late afternoon visits are recommended.
name: Oedolgae

excerpt: Museum featuring the works of late painter Lee Jung Seob in his restored former home.
detail_description: The Lee Jung Seob Art Gallery is a must-visit museum in Jeju, South Korea. It opened its doors in 1995 and offers a unique experience for art enthusiasts. The gallery showcases the masterpieces of Lee Jung-Seop, as well as paintings by renowned artists Park Soo-Keun and Lee Ung-No. Visitors can explore the restored former home of the late painter, gaining insight into his life on Jeju Island.
name: Lee Jung Seob Art Gallery

excerpt: Lively street named for a well-known artist who lived here, with art galleries, studios & cafes.
detail_description: Lee Jung Seop Street is a vibrant and culturally significant area in Seogwipo, known for its art galleries, studios, and cafes. It holds geographical importance as it was where the renowned Korean artist Lee Jung-Seop created some of his greatest paintings. The street hosts various events, festivals, and street concerts, making it a burgeoning center of culture and art.
name: Lee Jung Seop Street

excerpt: Scenic estuary lined with cliffs of volcanic rock, popular for kayaking & traditional-raft rides.
detail_description: Soesokkak, a famous tourist attraction in Jeju, is a scenic estuary known for its volcanic rock cliffs and popular activities like kayaking and traditional-raft rides. The area's name comes from the shape of a lying down cow, formed by the meeting of freshwater from Hyodoncheon Stream and saltwater. This hidden gem along Seogwipo spans seventy miles and offers breathtaking views reminiscent of landscapes in Oman and Japan.
name: Soesokkak

detail_description: Saeseom, also known as Sod Island, is a charming and tiny island located at the mouth of Seogwipo Harbour. Accessible via the picturesque cable-stayed Saeyeon-gyo bridge, this island offers a delightful boardwalk trail that takes less than an hour to complete. The well-maintained trail provides stunning views of the surrounding area, including Munseom Island. Despite its nickname as Bird Island, it may not always be teeming with avian life.
name: 새섬

detail_description: Wind 1947 offers an exhilarating cart riding experience on its 1,947m track, one of the longest in the country. The scenic views of Mount Halla add to the thrill. Unlike other vendors, Wind 1947 provides go-karts for two people, allowing you to enjoy the ride with a partner or child. The price is reasonable and there's a waiting area with a cafe and souvenir shop.
name: Wind 1947
address: 78-27 Topyeonggongdan-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: The Seogwipo Submarine offers a unique and unforgettable experience for tourists visiting Jeju. Descending to depths of 40m, this submarine allows you to marvel at the vibrant marine life surrounding the island. The activity is family-friendly, providing an adventure that is both enjoyable and safe. With English translations available during the commentary, visitors can fully appreciate the sights as they journey underwater.
name: Seogwipo Submarine 西歸浦谮水艇

excerpt: Rocky peak with a scenic hike, seasonal photo ops with yellow rapeseed blooms & a Buddhist temple.
detail_description: Sanbangsan, also known as Sunset Peak, is a rocky peak on Jeju Island with scenic hiking trails and seasonal photo opportunities with yellow rapeseed blooms. It features different trails, including one leading to the Sanbanggulsa cave temple about 150m above sea level. The area is surrounded by gardens and has a Buddhist temple at the foot of the hill.
name: Sanbangsan

excerpt: Museum dedicated to the history of technology of air & space travel, with a cafeteria & shops.
detail_description: The Jeju Aerospace Museum, the largest of its kind in Asia, is a captivating destination for aviation enthusiasts and families alike. It offers a comprehensive look into the history of air and space travel, with indoor and outdoor exhibits showcasing 26 aircraft. The museum also features interactive displays, hands-on activities for kids, and a flight simulator suitable for all ages.
name: Jeju Aerospace Museum
address: 218 Nokchabunjae-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Restored 1890s village featuring more than 100 structures & displays of period artifacts.
detail_description: Jeju Folk Village is a restored 1890s village that showcases over 100 structures and period artifacts. It's famous for being the filming site of the hit TV series Dae Jang Geum. The attraction features 117 houses depicting scenes from different village lives, including Mountain Village, Hill-Country Village, Fishing Village, and Shamanism Village. Visitors can explore traditional wedding halls and even enjoy horseback riding picture-taking zones.
name: Jeju Folk Village
address: 631-34 Minsokhaean-ro, Pyoseon-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Quiet, seafront beach area offering a lighthouse, restaurants & shops, plus scenic views & trails.
detail_description: Seopjikoji is a serene coastal area on the eastern shore of Jeju Island, offering a picturesque lighthouse, charming restaurants, and shops. The iconic Seopjikoji Lighthouse sits atop a hill with breathtaking ocean views and is locally believed to have wish-granting powers. This elegant white building has been featured in popular dramas and holds romantic significance for some.
name: Seopjikoji
address: Seopjikoji-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Glass-art theme park with indoor & outdoor displays, a children's forest & hands-on activities.
detail_description: Jeju Glass Castle is a unique glass art theme park in Jeju, featuring both indoor and outdoor displays, a children's forest, and hands-on activities. The park boasts the world's first all-glass labyrinth, as well as the world's largest glass ball and glass diamond among 250 delicate glass models exhibited in six themed model parks. Visitors can explore the exhibition hall to marvel at these intricate glass creations that give the place an ethereal vibe.
name: Jeju Glass Castle
address: 462 Nokchabunjae-ro, Hangyeong-myeon, Jeju-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Jeju Olle Trail Course 6 is a 13.3km route that offers a perfect balance of length and difficulty, making it one of the top attractions on Jeju Island. The trail takes about 4 hours to complete, offering diverse terrains with beaches, waterfalls, volcanoes, and monuments along the way. From Soesokkak to Jeju Olle Traveler Center, hikers can enjoy coastal views and stunning natural scenery while walking through mountain paths or trails.
name: Jeju Olle Trail Course 6

excerpt: A popular place to walk, this rocky coastline features unique cliff formations & scenic ocean views.
detail_description: Yongmeori Coast is a must-visit destination for nature enthusiasts. This rocky coastline offers stunning cliff formations and picturesque ocean views. The area is easily accessible by car, with the drive from Suweolbong to Sanbangsan and Yongmeori Coast taking around 30 minutes. Along the way, travelers can enjoy breathtaking coastal vistas and make stops for photo opportunities.
name: Yongmeori Coast
address: 112-3 Sagye-ri, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: National park with a large mountain, featuring many alpine plants, hiking trails & sweeping views.
detail_description: Hallasan National Park, located on Jeju Island in South Korea, is centered around the majestic Hallasan Mountain, the highest peak in the country. The mountain is surrounded by 368 parasitic volcanoes known as Oreums and offers sweeping views of the island. Designated as a national park in 1970, it is a haven for alpine plants and provides numerous hiking trails for outdoor enthusiasts to explore its geological wonders.
name: Hallasan National Park
